.TH "xemaclite_send_data" 9 "xemaclite_send_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xemaclite_send_data \- Send an Ethernet frame
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xemaclite_send_data
.BI "(struct net_local *drvdata "  ","
.BI "u8 *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int byte_count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drvdata" 12
Pointer to the Emaclite device private data
.IP "data" 12
Pointer to the data to be sent
.IP "byte_count" 12
Total frame size, including header
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function checks if the Tx buffer of the Emaclite device is free to send
data. If so, it fills the Tx buffer with data for transmission. Otherwise, it
returns an error.
.SH "RETURN"
0 upon success or -1 if the buffer(s) are full.
.SH "NOTE"
The maximum Tx packet size can not be more than Ethernet header
(14 Bytes) + Maximum MTU (1500 bytes). This is excluding FCS.
